            <h3>Finding Her Voice Again</h3>
            <p>
              When Margaret&rsquo;s family first came to us, they felt like they were losing her a
              little more each day. She had stopped speaking much, and the silence was heavy.
              But through gentle, patient work &mdash; music she once loved, photographs from
              her kitchen table, her daughter&rsquo;s steady voice reading old letters &mdash; something
              shifted. Margaret began to hum. Then she began to sing. And then, one afternoon,
              she looked at her daughter and said her name.
            </p>
            <p>
              This is the kind of moment we live for. Not a cure, but a connection. Not a fix,
              but a return to something true.
            </p>
            <a href="#" class="text-link" aria-label="Read the full story: Finding Her Voice Again">Read This Story &rarr;</a>
